{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — a unit test of only the prompt builder can miss failures in diff parsing + scoping glue code. REAL-INFRA: no external OS/network is required. MOCK-HIDE: yes, isolated mocks can hide incorrect wiring between parser and reviewer input assembly. LLM-DEP: no; this checks what is sent, not model quality.","test_description":"Run the real diff-ingestion and review-input assembly modules together on fixture PR diffs where unchanged file sections are large and changed hunks are small. Assert the constructed review payload contains only changed hunks (and allowed minimal context) and excludes unchanged regions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — GitHub diff-position semantics are easy to get wrong and mocks often accept invalid mappings. REAL-INFRA: yes — correctness boundary is real PR diff rendering/API behavior. MOCK-HIDE: yes — mocked API calls can pass while real API rejects/misplaces comments. LLM-DEP: no.","test_description":"Against a real test repository PR, post inline comments using computed positions for added/modified lines (including edge cases like multi-hunk files). Then fetch PR review comments via GitHub API and verify each lands on the intended file and diff line in the real PR.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.81,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — non-LLM heuristics/mocks cannot validate true model detection quality. REAL-INFRA: not primarily OS/API semantics; core risk is model judgment. MOCK-HIDE: yes — mocked model outputs trivially pass. LLM-DEP: yes — outcome depends on real model behavior and can vary run-to-run.","test_description":"Use a PR fixture with a seeded real bug (e.g., missing null check causing exception). Invoke the real model-based reviewer with production prompt/tooling and assert at least one finding correctly points to the seeded defect location/category. Track pass rate across repeated runs to detect instability.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — this is a cross-module consistency invariant (finding objects, posting results, summary assembly). REAL-INFRA: not strictly required to catch core mapping bug. MOCK-HIDE: yes if tests stub success everywhere; integration with realistic success/failure responses is needed. LLM-DEP: no, invariant is structural.","test_description":"Execute the finding-to-posting-to-summary pipeline with mixed posting outcomes (some inline posts succeed, some fail/reject) using a realistic adapter/fake store. Assert summary includes only findings with confirmed posted inline comment records and excludes unposted/failed ones.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment — completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — end-to-end sequencing failures (state handoff/retries/order) are often invisible in isolated tests. REAL-INFRA: yes — real PR/API interactions are required. LLM-DEP: yes — real review generation is part of completion. MULTI-STEP: yes — this is the full agent pipeline across multiple dependent steps.","test_description":"Run the automation unassisted on a real sandbox PR from trigger to completion: fetch diff, generate findings, post inline comments, then post top-level summary. Verify final PR state contains expected inline comments and one coherent summary, and that the run exits successfully without manual retries.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.19,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
